content.description: Sit start all the way left and traverse right across the lip on slopers and top out at the high point.
content.location: This is the obvious, rising traverse.

content.description: Sit start the obvious arête, and top out.
content.location: This boulder is located at the far end of the Pub Crawl Area. Keep the swamp on your left, cross the stone wall, and then move right about 150 feet to find this block.

content.description: Stand start on barely there slopers and a decent right foot, lock off, crank to the shelf, and top out.
content.location: Start about 3-4 feet right of the high point of the boulder.

content.description: Do a low sit start matched on the far left end of end of the decent flake shown in the bottom right corner of the photo. Power up on crimps, and top out right of the seam..The starting flake is definitely suspect, hence the name of the problem. Use your own judgment on this rig.
content.location: This boulder is located at the far end of the Pub Crawl Area. Follow the edge of the swamp almost to the stone wall. Then move right about 150 feet.

content.description: Sit start with hands matched on the decent flake and feet smeared on whatever, then make a big reach out to a right hand sidepull and then head  up to the obvious shelf and top out. This is more of a one and half star problem.
content.protection: Pad, but it has a good landing.
content.location: It is just right of the problem Last Call.  Start on the obvious flake near the bottom of the undercut face.

content.description: Pub Boulder is one good block with a great, rising traverse.
